<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> The purpose of this Directive is to lay down safety standards for seagoing fishing vessels of 24 metres in length and over, both new, and existing, in so far as the Annex to the Torremolinos Protocol applies to the latter, and </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esoleva direktiivi eesm&auml;rk on kehtestada ohutusnormid nii uutele kui ka olemasolevatele merekalalaevadele, mille pikkus on v&auml;hemalt 24 meetrit, kuiv&otilde;rd Torremolinose protokolli lisa kehtib olemasolevate suhtes, ja mis: </eesti>
<inglise> - flying the flag of a Member State and registered in the Community, or </inglise>
<eesti> - s&otilde;idavad liikmesriigi lipu all ning on registreeritud &uuml;henduses v&otilde;i </eesti>
<inglise> - operating in the internal waters or territorial sea of a Member State, or </inglise>
<eesti> - tegutsevad liikmesriigi sisevetes v&otilde;i territoriaalmeres v&otilde;i </eesti>
<inglise> - landing their catch in the port of a Member State. </inglise>
<eesti> - lossivad oma saagi liikmesriigi sadamas. </eesti>
<inglise> Recreational craft engaged in non-commercial fishing are excluded from the scope of this Directive. </inglise>
